parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor can cause the windshield to fog up, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents, especially in rainy or cold weather. Additionally, the lack of air circulation can lead to driver discomfort and distraction.
symptoms: The blower motor operates intermittently
sometimes turning on and sometimes not
the blower motor fails to turn on
the windshield fogs up
inability to defrost windshield and side windows
driver distraction
discomfort
and distraction from high heat in the cabin.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of malfunctions, including the windshield wipers, horn, check engine light, and dash lights, which can lead to accidents or fires.
symptoms: Strong odor of electrical wiring burning
windshield wipers
horn
check engine light
and dash lights malfunction
smoke coming from the dash
flames evident from the dash and front area of the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the car to stall while driving, increasing the risk of accidents, and the failure of the transmission system can cause difficulty shifting gears, leading to loss of control.
symptoms: Ignition turns off while driving
transmission does not go into gear properly
difficulty shifting into drive or reverse
constant need to check the shifter to ensure correct gear
rolling of the car on hills when in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shifting issues can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to engage into gear, leading to hazardous situations, especially in traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift into gear
the vehicle stalls
the transmission does not engage into reverse gear
the vehicle moves unexpectedly while in park
the shifter is stuck in park or drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Issues - Intermittent Blower Motor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the blower motor can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, and potentially lead to a vehicle fire.
symptoms: The heater/AC blower motor fails to power on
the blower motor stops working while driving
the blower motor can be restarted by rapping on the dash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of the headlamps can cause reduced visibility and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlamps fail to function
the headlamps need to be replaced frequently
the headlamp fixtures do not seal correctly.
